Data Types: int, string, float, dict, list, tuple

Variable type is dynamic and can be changed any time
use type() to get type of variable

String indexing & Splicing - 
Indexing example - 
a=Hello, a[2] =l, a[-1]=o
"Hello World"[-3] = r

Splicing [star:stop:jump] - 
[:] - means include everything from start to stop
[:3] - everything from beginning until 2. end limit is excluded.
[4:] - starting from 4 and everything until end
stop is not included. stop index is excluded
jump is no. characters to skip
